Steps to install SASS on macOS:

1. First, ensure you have Node.js installed. If not, install it from nodejs.org or using Homebrew:
   brew install node

2. Check Node.js version:
   node --version

3. Install SASS globally using npm:
   npm install -g sass@3.7.4

4. Verify SASS installation:
   sass --version

5. If you encounter permission issues, use sudo:
   sudo npm install -g sass@3.7.4

6. Alternative: Install SASS locally in your project directory:
   cd /path/to/alx-intermediate-frontend/0x03-sass_scss
   npm install sass@3.7.4

7. To use local installation, run SASS with npx:
   npx sass input.scss output.css
